rComments: Professor Wania is an amazing lecturer! His ability to engage students for 3 consecutive hours is truly superior. He likes to write on the board so you MUST attend lectures and take good notes. He does not post any powerpoint slides. The TA was also very helpful and approachable. Overall, a very challenging course but you get to learn so much!

rComments: He explains everything so nicely and logically, probably one of my favourite profs so far. He may be monotone, but that didn't bother me. His way of speaking is very monotone, so it's difficult to stay tuned to what he's saying. He's a good prof because he follows the textbook, so if you're confused, read the textbook for further explanations!
Great professor, others may say he is not clear but I personally think he is and was able to teach effectively. Exam was good and fair. Study the mock midterm he posts at the end of the module.

rComments: He makes everything super clear by going through examples and is very clear in the types of questions he expects from you and the content he wants you to know. The midterm was fairly easy and he was super nice if you were to approach him for questions.
